{
  "stem": "12494.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my dad sort of used me as [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] partly his errand boy, partly his aide in a variety of activities that were needed to support these people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And as time went on, after 1942, I became increasingly aware of what was going on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had refugees who told us about what was going on in Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And these were refugees from a variety of camps.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Some of them were-- were non-Jewish refugees.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father was a very close friend of a refugee Polish general who was, of course, not Jewish-- there were no Jewish generals in Poland-- but who maintained contact with Poland and who reported on what was going on.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I guess to summarize it, from-- [INAUDIBLE], these were parallel developments.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I grew up from being a kid to becoming a young man to understand these things.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the information was coming in, and I gradually assimilated the information.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm not sure whether I'm answering your question, but by-- I would say by the time that I graduated from the gymnasium in June, 1943, I think that I was very informed on what was going on.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what was your sense of that?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, on the one hand, of course, it was a sense of horror and lack of understanding, and, at the beginning, lack of belief.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Quite a few of us were not quite as close to activities as I was-- and I was only because of my father-- but most Hungarian Jews simply rejected the information.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They simply didn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They felt that such a thing is impossible in the 20th century.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this belief lasted until beyond the German-- German occupation.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
